	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />In fact, if you have Famicom expansion sound available, porting an MP3 replacement music system might be <em>easier</em> than running Lua on a coprocessor because an MP3 player chip can present an interface much like that of the <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=762" class="postlink">Japanese version of Bases Loaded</a>.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
